<paragraph blockId="7.[192,1440,807,1060]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,278,807,831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Notes.</emphasis>
Specimens of this species in 
<collectionCode box="[655,740,807,831]" collectionName="USA, Washington D.C., National Museum of Natural History, [formerly, United States National Museum]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
were tentatively identified by Paul D. Hurd as 
<emphasis box="[1356,1375,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">X</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasilianorum" subGenus="Neoxylocopa">
(
<emphasis box="[1402,1424,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">N</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[192,371,839,863]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">brasilianorum</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
, a similarly-colored species which is otherwise known from localities in southern Brazil which are outside the Amazon basin (
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd, P. D., Jr." box="[867,1004,872,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" refId="ref11357" refString="Hurd, P. D., Jr. 1978. An annotated catalog of the carpenter bees (Genus Xylocopa Latreille) of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Smithsonian Institution Press; Washington, DC. 106 p." type="book" year="1978">Hurd 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[1018,1170,872,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref11899" refString="Moure, J. S. 2003. Uma especie nova de Xylocopa Latreille, 1802, e notas sobre Xylocopa transitoria Perez e X. mordax Smith (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 47 (1): 71 - 74." type="journal article" year="2003">Moure 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The brief discussion and reports of 
<emphasis box="[367,386,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">X</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[409,431,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">N</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[453,589,904,928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">submordax</emphasis>
Cockerell from the Amazon basin by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; J. M. F. Camargo" box="[1041,1374,905,929]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="209 - 214" refId="ref12023" refString="Moure, J. S., and J. M. F. Camargo. 1988. Uma nova especie de Xylocopa (Neoxylocopa) do Brasil (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 32 (2): 209 - 214." type="journal article" year="1988">Moure and Camargo (1988)</bibRefCitation>
refer instead to this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[477,628,938,962]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref11899" refString="Moure, J. S. 2003. Uma especie nova de Xylocopa Latreille, 1802, e notas sobre Xylocopa transitoria Perez e X. mordax Smith (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 47 (1): 71 - 74." type="journal article" year="2003">Moure 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The true 
<emphasis box="[761,780,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">X</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[803,825,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">N</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[849,985,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">submordax</emphasis>
was placed in synonymy with 
<emphasis box="[1360,1379,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">X</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Perez" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transitoria" subGenus="Neoxylocopa">
(
<emphasis box="[1402,1424,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">N</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[192,323,970,993]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">transitoria</emphasis>
Pérez
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[444,610,970,994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref11899" refString="Moure, J. S. 2003. Uma especie nova de Xylocopa Latreille, 1802, e notas sobre Xylocopa transitoria Perez e X. mordax Smith (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 47 (1): 71 - 74." type="journal article" year="2003">Moure (2003)</bibRefCitation>
; specimens of this latter species in 
<collectionCode box="[1043,1128,970,994]" collectionName="USA, Washington D.C., National Museum of Natural History, [formerly, United States National Museum]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
all have greenish-blue or bluish-violet wing iridescence and are from localities in northern South America and the Caribbean which are located outside the Amazon basin.
</paragraph>
